  "local_port": 49870,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much should I aim in my graduation to get into IIM A/B/C assuming I get a 99+ percentile in CAT?",
  "response": "Achieving admission to the prestigious Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) such as IIM Ahmedabad, Bangalore, or Calcutta is highly competitive, even with a stellar CAT score. While a 99+ percentile in the CAT is an excellent start, your undergraduate academic performance plays a crucial role in strengthening your application. Here\u2019s a detailed breakdown of what you should aim for in your graduation to maximize your chances of admission:\n\n### **1. Academic Performance (CGPA/Percentage):**\n\n- **High CGPA/Percentage:** Aim for a **minimum of 8.0 out of 10** (or the equivalent percentage, typically **80% and above**) in your undergraduate studies. However, securing a higher CGPA, such as **8.5/10 or above**, can significantly enhance your profile, especially for top IIMs like Ahmedabad and Bangalore.\n\n- **Consistency Across Semesters:** Ensure consistent academic performance across all semesters. IIMs look for candidates who demonstrate sustained excellence rather than sporadic high performance.\n\n- **Relevance of Major:** While IIMs accept candidates from diverse academic backgrounds (engineering, commerce, arts, sciences, etc.), excelling in your core subject can showcase your ability to handle rigorous academic challenges.\n\n### **2. Academic Rigor and Reputation of Institution:**\n\n- **Tier of Your Undergraduate Institution:** Graduating from a reputed and rigorous academic institution can be advantageous. If your college is known for its high academic standards, it adds value to your CGPA.\n\n- **Course Difficulty:** Engaging in a challenging curriculum and performing well can reflect your capability to manage the demanding coursework at IIMs.\n\n### **3. Academic Achievements and Honors:**\n\n- **Awards and Recognitions:** Any academic awards, scholarships, or honors received during your undergraduate studies can bolster your application.\n\n- **Research and Projects:** Involvement in significant projects, research papers, or publications demonstrates initiative and depth of knowledge in your field.\n\n### **4. Extracurricular and Leadership Activities:**\n\nWhile academic excellence is paramount, IIMs also value holistic candidates who showcase leadership, teamwork, and extracurricular involvement. Engaging in clubs, sports, student government, or community service can set you apart.\n\n### **5. Additional Considerations:**\n\n- **Internships and Work Experience:** Relevant internships or work experience can provide practical insights and enhance your application.\n\n- **Statement of Purpose and Essays:** Clearly articulate how your academic background, experiences, and career goals align with what IIMs offer.\n\n- **Letters of Recommendation:** Strong endorsements from professors or employers who can vouch for your academic and professional capabilities add significant weight.\n\n### **Summary of Targets:**\n\n- **CGPA/Percentage:** Aim for **8.5/10 or above** (or equivalent)\n- **Class Rank:** Being in the **top 10-20 percentile** of your graduating class can be beneficial\n- **Institution Reputation:** Preferably from a well-recognized and academically rigorous institution\n- **Holistic Profile:** Complement your academic excellence with strong extracurriculars, leadership roles, and relevant experiences\n\n### **Final Thoughts**\n\nWhile academic performance is a critical component of your IIM application, remember that admissions committees evaluate candidates holistically. Balancing strong academics with meaningful extracurricular involvement, leadership experiences, and a clear career vision will position you as a compelling candidate for IIM Ahmedabad, Bangalore, or Calcutta.\n\nGood luck with your preparations!",
